node.text:
After both of their siblings died and weeks of quarantine, Woody and Ethel finally met! Not sure it was the epic love story we all imagined 😂

Sweet little Woody is growing up, he was neutered and microchipped last Friday and he heads to his forever home at the end of next week! There might be tears on my end.

Until then, he has Ethel to keep him on his toes!

#IndianSpringsKitties #fosteringsaveslives #adoptdontshop #spayandneuter #LucyAndEthelKittkes #fosterkittens #catsofinstagram #kittens

node.text:
Poor Ethel misses her sister. I really want to put her in with Woody but I’m so strict on quarantine. I just wonder if she could have anything she could pass to him. I doubt it. She’s displaying zero symptoms of being ill.

Until then, she’s taking comfort in Grandma Blanche’s favorite bed.

Thank you for all the messages of love and support. I’m always hesitant to share the bad parts of fostering because I never want to discourage anyone from fostering.  We take in the most critical cases to foster. Not all kittens are this complicated and need this much care. There are easy foster kitties out there that just need a safe place to stay temporarily until they are ready for adoption.

#fosterkitten #LucyAndEthelKitties

node.text:
From the streets of Las Vegas, fo loving homes in the Pacific Northwest/Canada. 76 cats are heading to their forever homes! Spayed/neutered/vaccinated/microchip and healthy. Leaving behind at 76 open kennels for us to save more.

Thank you to all who donated to make this happen and thank you most of all to @greatergoodcharities and @iheartcatscom

@heartsaliveanimalrescue

#fosteringsaveslives #adoptdontshop #spayandneuter

node.text:
You definitely don’t need an entire room to be able to foster kittens. A spare bathroom, a pet playpen or even an extra large dog kennel works great.

I also don’t give kittens access to things that I can’t easily disinfect or throw away (more expensive cat scratchers or cat condos) until I know they are healthy. I make sure that they don’t have anything they can spread (diarrhea, fungus, URI, etc.) before I give them access to these things.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nikki Martinez on August 16, 2021. May be an image of cat.

node.text:
SURPRISE!

Yesterday I was heading to drop off Portobella at the @heartsaliveanimalrescue adoption center. It broke my heart, but I needed more exposure for her and I figured if people walked into the adoption center they would see her in person and could fill out an application to adopt.

On my way I received a text message from Chickadee’s (renamed Sundae) wonderful new family. They said they couldn’t stop thinking about Portobella and wondered if she found a family yet. I burst into tears! THIS is what I wanted for! This is the home she needed. I told them I was headed to the rescue to drop her off and they said, “no way! We will get her room ready right now!”

Today they signed the adoption contract and named her Shay. Here she is in the arms of her new family!

This is what fostering is about.

#fosteringsaveslives #adoptdontshop #spayandneuter #fungusamonguskitties #kitten #adopted #foreverfamily

node.text:
“Hi! My name is Portobella, but you can call me Bella. I’m about 3 months old and still looking for my forever home. I am a sweet girl and I’ve learned to trust people. I am a little tiny bit shy when you first approach me, but the minute you pick me up and put me in your lap I start to purr and I am so happy. I really love the cats in my foster home and I love playing with toys. I am in Las Vegas, but can be transported to Southern California on Monday! PLEASE choose me.”

#adoptme #kittenforadoption #spayandneuter #adoptdontshop

node.text:
IN HONOR OF STANLEY…

Yesterday was a huge success! Hard-working C5 trappers made a special effort to trap in honor of Stanley, knowing that the best way to prevent kittens being born on the street to suffer is to spay/neuter and stop it at the source.

42 cats were brought into the @heartsaliveanimalclinic (one ended up already having an ear tip so he got to sit back and relax in the air conditioning).

Remember my friend Jesse who was babysitting Stanley for me while I was away? I invited him to come to see what was being done in Stanley’s honor and I’m so happy that he was able to make it and see this wonderful event for himself (I snapped a photo of him standing next to the cats in traps).

And best yet?! Our Instagram LIVE raised enough money to cover ALL the surgery costs for this event! THANK YOU to all who donated!

A true team effort to honor a special little boy. @c5tnrlv 

#TNRworks #trapneuterreturn #spayandneuter #feralcat #kittenseason #neighborhoodcat

node.text:
Caught the last two cats in this colony FOR STANLEY!

A few months ago I trapped and entire colony, or so I thought. The woman feeding the cats in the colony said she thought there might be two kittens under the shed, but she didn’t ever see them regularly. I told her to let me know if she saw them. I checked in from time to time, but she rarely saw them.

She called me about a week ago and told me that they have been hanging around and they were a little bit older now. I didn’t know what night I had time to go trap them. Not gonna lie, it was a super long day today and I was really tired, definitely not in the mood to go trapping but…I needed to for Stanley and his spay/neuter clinic tomorrow.

I drove to the other side of town and set up my drop trap. Foster Papi got off work and picked up some fried chicken and met me there. We don’t eat chicken, but we know the cats can’t resist it and we weren’t playing around!

Got ‘em! In honor of Stanley.

Join me tomorrow morning LIVE to see all the cats the hard-working volunteer trappers at C5 have caught for the spay/neuter clinic tomorrow!

#InHonorofStanley #TNR #spayandneuter

node.text:
Grab your tissues for this bittersweet post.

As we all know, former foster Stanley passed away a few weeks ago after being diagnosed with a congenital birth defect. After a team of specialists gathered together to review his symptoms and tests, they strongly suspected he either had a twisted lobe in his lung or a hernia in his diaphragm and recommended euthanasia. A devastating loss for our sweet boy who enjoyed life.

Over the past several weeks, Hearts Alive Village Animal Clinic has been preparing to ramp up spay and neuter surgeries, realizing that spay/neuter is the way to get to the root of the cat overpopulation issue. Dr. Ken at the HAV Veterinary Clinic recommended that they do their biggest clinic day to date tomorrow, spaying and neutering 50 stray/unowned cats trapped by C5 and that it be done in honor of our boy Stanley.

When Christy, the Executive Director called me last week to tell me this, I was at the grocery store and I immediately broke down sobbing. The kittens that come into shelters and rescues don’t deserve the life they were dealt.  Spaying and neutering 50 cats will prevent countless generations of cats born on the street only to suffer.

Join me on Instagram LIVE tomorrow morning! I’ll be at the @heartsaliveanimalclinic tomorrow showing you the behind-the-scenes spay/neuter process.

THANK YOU to those who donated to Hearts Alive Village and C5 in his honor because you made this happen! @heartsaliveanimalrescue @c5tnrlv

#InHonorOfStanley #spayandneuter #TNR
